Parliament, Tuesday, 22 May 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow be briefed by National Treasury on the consolidated report on deviations and expansions of national departments and entities for the first quarter of 2018. Details of the meeting: Date: Wednesday, 23 May 2018
	Time: 09:00
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI For media enquiries, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
